She has won a series of prestigious junior titles including the Easter Bowl Championships, USTA International Spring Championships, and the Coffee Bowl.​ She's also playing the U.S. Open junior tournament. 

Cici's amateur status means she is unable to claim the more than 60,000 US dollars in prize money for a first-round victory, but she is in no rush to turn professional.

She said: 'I think I'm definitely going to stay an amateur right now to keep my options open for college, in case an injury or something happens. But I'd love to be a pro one day.'

Cici's wild card wasn't charity, she earned it when she won the USTA Girls' 18s National Championship, becoming the youngest to win the title since Lindsay Davenport, according to Sports Illustrated. 

